name: amoxicillin
description: A penicillin in which the substituent at position 6 of the penam ring is a 2-amino-2-(4-hydroxyphenyl)acetamido group.

name: ampicillin
description: A penicillin in which the substituent at position 6 of the penam ring is a 2-amino-2-phenylacetamido group.

name: carbenicillin
description: A penicillin antibiotic having a 6beta-2-carboxy-2-phenylacetamido side-chain.

name: methicillin
description: A penicillin that is 6-aminopenicillanic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens is replaced by a 2,6-dimethoxybenzoyl group.

name: piperacillin
description: A penicillin in which the substituent at position 6 of the penam ring is a 2-[(4-ethyl-2,3-dioxopiperazin-1-yl)carboxamido]-2-phenylacetamido group.

name: ticarcillin
description: A penicillin compound having a 6beta-[(2R)-2-carboxy-2-thiophen-3-ylacetyl]amino side-group.

name: penicillin
description: Any member of the group of substituted penams containing two methyl substituents at position 2, a carboxylate substituent at position 3 and a carboxamido group at position 6.

name: allergen
description: A chemical compound, or part thereof, which causes the onset of an allergic reaction by interacting with any of the molecular pathways involved in an allergy.

name: benzylpenicillin
description: A penicillin in which the substituent at position 6 of the penam ring is a phenylacetamido group.

name: penicillin allergen
description: Any penicillin which causes the onset of an allergic reaction.
